    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA305-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu naṟṟāy tōḻikkuc colliyatu. 2. maṉaimaruṭciyumām.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is what the real mother said to the confidante. 2. It is also the confusion of the house.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA305">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>variyaṇi pantum vāṭiya vayalaiyu</l>
<l>mayilaṭi yaṉṉa mākkura ṉocciyuṅ</l>
<l>kaṭiyuṭai viyaṉakark kāṇvarat tōṉṟat</l>
<l>tamiyēṉ kaṇṭataṇ ṭalaiyun teṟuvara</l>
<l>nōyā kiṉṟē makaḷainiṉ ṟōḻi</l>
<l>yericiṉan taṇinta vilaiyi lañciṉai</l>
<l>varippuṟap puṟaviṉ pulampuko ṭeḷviḷi</l>
<l>yuruppavi ramaiyat tamarppaṉa ṇōkki</l>
<l>yilaṅkilai veḷvēl viṭalaiyai</l>
<l>vilaṅkumalai yāriṭai naliyuṅko leṉavē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The line-adorned ball and the faded Vayalai</l>
<l>and the Nocci with big ears as a peacock’s foot,</l>
<l rend="indent">when these appear for [my eyes] to see<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kāṇ vara</term>: how to account for <term xml:lang="ta">vara</term> here? "So that [I] come (= happen) to see [them]"?</note> in the well-protected wide</l>
<l rend="indent">mansion,</l>
<l rend="indent">and the cool place seen by me who am solitary, scorchingly(?)</l>
<l>they have become pain, o daughter:<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">makaḷai</term>: T.V.G. explains here the -<term xml:lang="ta">ai</term> as expletive, but it seems as well possible to take it as a mark of the 2nd person, an address.</note></l>
<l rend="indent4">“your friend,</l>
<l>will she torment on the difficult way through the transverse mountains</l>
<l rend="indent">the young man with white spear with a shining leaf,</l>
<l rend="indent">looking like<note place="foot">Here we have to understand <term xml:lang="ta">nōkki</term> as an extended word of comparison or instead take HIM as the subject who is looking at HER.</note> one who is at strife on the occasion of shining heat</l>
<l rend="indent2">with the clear sound conveying loneliness of the dove with striped back</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the leafless pretty branch as the anger of the flame has come down?”</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
